Query like in mining, these choose what type of rock you want to work with, ps, hs, a, etc. Text contentn means to just add a text onto the rocks you choose.
unless when you are selecting the thing you want to select, you have to make them =. 
let myheading = document.querySelector('h1');
myheading.textContent = 'hello world';
OR
another short way will be to just add all on one line
document.querySelector("html").textContent = "Hello World"
Remember to call the document to let them know. 

here is an example of using the query selection with an onclick on the html
document.querySelector('html').onclick = function() {
    alert('Ouch! Stop poking me!');
}

Here we are using the attribute function, so things next to the main query ones. Also, setting a variable equal to the document.qure.... etc, is important since it will be
referenced alot. 
let myImage = document.querySelector('img');

myImage.onclick = function() {
    let mySrc = myImage.getAttribute('src');
    if(mySrc === 'images/firefox-icon.png') {
      myImage.setAttribute ('src','images/firefox2.png');
    } else {
      myImage.setAttribute ('src','images/firefox-icon.png');
    }
}
